id: pm-j15d
title: Extract shared extension fixture writer for tests
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: extension/package tests repeat fixture creation for manifest.json plus trivial index.js/index.mjs entrypoints. Representative copies include tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts:6 createProjectExtension, tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts:31 createProjectExtension, tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts:18 createProjectExtension, tests/unit/extension-loader.spec.ts:26 createExtension, tests/unit/extension-command-github.spec.ts:19 writeMockExtension, tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts:15 createExtension, and many inline manifest/index writes in tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts. Existing pm-eltf covers item factories, not extension fixture setup."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: code-quality,dedup,extensions,tests
created_at: "2026-05-22T19:17:37.412Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T19:58:49.531Z"
author: codex-duplicate-audit
acceptance_criteria: "A shared writeTestExtension/createTestExtension helper supports project/global/source roots, entry filename, capabilities, and custom entry source; repeated local extension fixture writers are removed where they do not clarify test intent; extension/package tests and pnpm build pass."
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Shared extension fixture helper extracted and merged in PR #52.
expected_result: Extension/package tests keep the same behavior while duplicate manifest and entrypoint fixture setup is centralized.
actual_result: "tests/helpers/extensions.ts now backs representative extension fixtures; focused tests, full release gate, manual dogfood, GitHub checks, and AI review follow-up passed."
